-- Mercedes’s Hamilton Wins Pole Position for F-1 German Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-07-07T04:16:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-06/mercedes-s-hamilton-wins-pole-position-for-f-1-german-grand-prix.html
Lewis Hamilton  of Mercedes beat out
Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel to claim pole position for today’s
German Grand Prix.  Britain’s Hamilton had a time of 1 minute, 29.398 seconds
at the Nurburgring to take his second consecutive pole and third
of the season. Defending world champion Vettel of Germany was
one-tenth of a second behind Hamilton.  Red Bull’s Mark Webber and Lotus teammates Kimi Raikkonen
and Romain Grosjean rounded out the top-five qualifiers.  Vettel leads the season standings with 132 points after
eight of 19 races. Ferrari’s  Fernando Alonso , who qualified
eighth yesterday, is second with 111 points, followed by
Raikkonen with 98 and Hamilton with 89.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  